The paper presents a new approach that relies on semantic web technologies and models to assist collaboration among the members of a neurosciences community. This involves deriving and sharing semantic web service specifications from neuroscientists' requirements to perform image processing pipelines. The use of semantic web technologies and models suggests a strong focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Additionally, the paper deals with image processing pipelines, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of deep learning, which is a sub-field of machine learning and falls under the cs.DL sub-category.
